race.comment: Shades of Sydney staying races with C J Waller loading the bases and his three all look to have chances. First emergency ROYAL OPTIMISM (11) put the writing on the wall first-up with an eye-catching performance. Would have won in another 10 metres and actually gets an extra 468m so should be tough to beat with luck in running. BORN SURVIVOR (1) fought on for second last start over 1600m at Hanging Rock, making it two minor placings in a row. Meets some better types this time but a win is not out of the question. GOLDEN MASK (2) ran a much-improved last start, which was here, so he obviously likes the track and can improve again. ANGEL FEET (4) can improve again here out in trip.
